Package: gradepath
Type: Package
Title: Discrimination Report Cards via a Native Kline-Rose-Walters Core
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R:
    person("JoonHo", "Lee", email = "jlee296@ua.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0006-4019-8703"))
Description: Replicates the discrimination-report-card analysis of Kline,
    Rose, and Walters (2024) <doi:10.1257/aer.20230700>, "A Discrimination
    Report Card", entirely in R. A single package replaces the original
    multi-language pipeline ('Stata', R, 'Python', 'MATLAB', and 'Gurobi'),
    reproducing the estimation core natively: beta-GMM precision
    standardization, empirical-Bayes prior deconvolution and posterior
    shrinkage, the pairwise outranking matrix, the Bayes-risk grade integer
    program, and the information-reliability frontier. The grade program is
    solved with 'Gurobi' by default or the open 'HiGHS' backend, so the
    workflow runs without commercial solver access. Outputs include discrete
    integer-grade report cards, the four signature figures of the paper, and a
    Monte Carlo calibration check. Low-level empirical-Bayes primitives are
    supplied through the 'ebrecipe' package behind a controlled seam, as an
    input container and one-level cross-check rather than a stage orchestrator.
    This is a pre-release: the one-level race and gender core (M1) is accepted
    under a predeclared scoped policy, recovering the published grade
    distributions as proven-optimal solves, while the two-level industry
    surface (M2) is partially accepted, with exact industry grade counts
    reproduced and some continuous rows resting on fixture-parity evidence
    rather than direct reproduction. Applied researchers can run, audit, and
    extend the KRW analysis with standard R tooling.
URL: https://github.com/joonho112/gradepath,
    https://joonho112.github.io/gradepath/
